text: Dean Benson Phillips (born January 20, 1969) is an American businessman and politician who has served as the U.S. Representative from Minnesota's 3rd congressional district from 2019 to 2025. In July 2023, it was reported that Phillips was considering challenging President Joe Biden in the 2024 Democratic presidential primaries. He officially announced his candidacy on October 26, 2023. On March 6, 2024, Phillips suspended his campaign following Super Tuesday. ==References== Category:1969 births Category:Living people Category:United States representatives from Minnesota Category:Politicians from Saint Paul, Minnesota Category:Democratic Party (United States) politicians Category:Businesspeople from Minnesota Category:2024 United States presidential candidates
